Home Screen: Select one of the sets and a hierarchy level at the top, then click on a volume name to open the volume.

Dictionaries: Four dictionaries are included in the Android Tipitaka, the PED, the CPED, the CEPD and the DPPN. Use the Velthuis scheme to look up words starting with a string (use * for wildcards within or at the beginning of the word). If no match is found, the app will check for base words from declensions (e.g. searching for "buddho" will give a definition of "buddha").

English (ATI): Android Tipitaka can incorporate the offline archive from Access to Insight (
http://www.accesstoinsight.org/tech/download/bulk/bulk.html ) to allow browsing of their suttas and other articles of interest, as well as bookmarking pages for later reference. Clicking on the "English" menu item while reading from the sutta pitaka will take you directly to the section of ATI\'s site regarding the nikaya you are reading.

Reading: Once a volume is open, it will initially show an index which is opened and closed using the "Index" menu item. Navigate to a section by clicking on an index entry. When reading a section, swiping a finger left or right across the text moves backwards or forwards in the sections. Highlighting a word (only available in later versions of Android) causes a "Dictionaries" button to appear, which allows to look up a word in the dictionaries, which recognize declensions as well. Bookmark using the "Bookmark" button when viewing a section.
Search: The search button allows you to search for a word or phrase in selected texts; use the Velthuis scheme (e.g. "aa", ".t", etc.) for diacritics.
